The first step to installing Drupal 7 is to download
the latest released copy of Drupal 7 in tar.gz format.
Go to drupal.org and click on the
button. As of this writing the latest version is 7.9, but that will change.

You’ll be taken to a page that lists a number of releases. You want to download the tar.gz version of the version 7.x recommended release. In the screenshot below the release number is 7.9, but it will increase to 7.10, 7.11, and beyond.
Download the file to your computer.

At this point, you are ready to upload your zipped copy of the latest recommended release of Drupal to your web host. There is no need for you to unzip your copy of Drupal on your local machine. In fact the installation will go much more swiftly and reliably if you do not.
